1938;;The Adventures of Tom Sawyer;;American;;Norman Taurog, William A. Wellman;;Tommy Kelly, Jackie Moran, Victor Jory;;adventure;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Adventures_of_Tom_Sawyer_(1938_film);;The United Artists release includes most of the sequences familiar to readers of the book, including the fence-whitewashing episode; a wild raft ride down the Mississippi River; Tom and Huckleberry Finn's attendance at their own funeral, after the boys, who were enjoying an adventure on a remote island, are presumed dead; the murder trial of local drunkard Muff Potter; and Tom and Becky Thatcher's flight through a cave as they try to escape from Injun Joe, who is revealed to be the real killer.